article.headline: Coppin St 59, Florida A&M 55
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Darryl Roberts scored 15 points to lead Coppin State to a 59-55 win against Florida A&M on Saturday. Nicholas King and Darryl Proctor scored 10 points each for Coppin State (5-10, 5-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Coppin State scored 22 points off of turnovers. They also went 26-of-36 from the free-throw line, compared to Florida A&M's shooting 9-of-11 from the line. Henry Colter led Coppin State in rebounds with seven. Coppin State won despite shooting only about 30 percent from the field, compared to about 48 percent for Florida A&M. Florida A&M (3-9, 2-3) was led by Darius Glover, who scored 16 points. Tony Tate scored 12 points and had seven assists, but only managed to go 2-of-10 in 3-point shots. James Pattman led Florida A&M in rebounds with six. Florida A&M led at halftime 30-22, but Coppin State came back to outscore Florida A&M 37-25 in the second half.
